Alternatively, the repertoires may be cloned sequentially into the same vector, e.g. as described in 
Barbas et al., Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 88: 7978-7982 (1991
), or assembled together by PCR and then cloned, e.g. as described in 
Clackson et al., Nature, 352: 624-628 (1991
). PCR assembly can also be used to join VH and VL DNAs with DNA encoding a flexible peptide spacer to form single chain Fv (scFv) repertoires. In yet another technique, "in cell PCR assembly" is used to combine VH and VL genes within lymphocytes by PCR and then clone repertoires of linked genes as described in 
Embleton et al., Nucl. Acids Res., 20: 3831-3837 (1992
).






