Various techniques have been developed for the production of antibody fragments. Traditionally, these fragments were derived via proteolytic digestion of intact antibodies (
Morimoto et al (1992) Journal of Biochemical and Biophysical Methods 24:107-117
; and 
Brennan et al (1985) Science, 229:81
